                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/123.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that his Government is sending Secretary
                    of Legation at Habana, Mr. Cardenas, to El Paso arriving there evening 17th
                    instant to learn condition and render assistance to suffering Spaniards at
                    Chihuahua. Minister for Foreign Affairs wishes that Cardenas may communicate
                    direct and cooperate with our Consuls there and elsewhere. Please advise me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
